The paper focuses on predicting the long-term citation count for individual publications, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model uses recurrent neural network with long short-term memory units, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and deep learning (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of recency effect, which is relevant to social media and online communities (cs.SI).
